*[Bug 18989] Wishlist: provide conversion of POSIXlt time zone retaining sub-second accuracy*
<https://bugs.r-project.org/show_bug.cgi?id=18989>

--- Comment #7 from Suharto Anggono (<mailto:suharto_anggono@yahoo.com|suharto_anggono@yahoo.com>) ---
(In reply to Suharto Anggono from comment #6)
Without defining `POSIXltconv',

    tz &lt;- attr(x, "tzone")
    value &lt;- unCfillPOSIXlt(
        if(inherits(value, "POSIXlt") &amp;&amp; identical(tz, attr(value, "tzone")))
            value
        else as.POSIXlt(as.POSIXct(value), tz = tz[1L]))

could become

    tz1 &lt;- function(x) {  # like in .check_tzones()
        y &lt;- attr(x, "tzone")
        if(is.null(y)) "" else y[1L]
    }
    tz &lt;- tz1(x)
    if(is.character(value) || is.factor(value)) value &lt;- as.POSIXlt(value)
    if(inherits(value, "POSIXlt")) {
        if(tz1(value) == tz) # can be NA?
            value &lt;- unCfillPOSIXlt(value)
        else {
            s &lt;- value$sec - floor(value$sec)
            value &lt;- unclass(as.POSIXlt(as.POSIXct(value), tz = tz))
            if(length(s) != (n &lt;- length(value$sec))) s &lt;- rep_len(s, n)
            if(length(n &lt;- which(is.finite(value$sec) &amp; s != 0))
                value$sec[n] &lt;- floor(value$sec[n]) + s[n]
        }
    } else value &lt;- unclass(as.POSIXlt(as.POSIXct(value), tz = tz))

In `[[&lt;-.POSIXlt`, because `value` should be just one element, the code inside
`if(inherits(value, "POSIXlt"))` could also be

        if(tz1(value) == tz) # can be NA?
            value &lt;- unclass(value)
        else {
            s &lt;- value$sec - floor(value$sec)
            value &lt;- unclass(as.POSIXlt(as.POSIXct(value), tz = tz))
            if(is.finite(value$sec) &amp;&amp; s != 0)
                value$sec &lt;- floor(value$sec) + s
        }

